This license lets others remix, adapt, and build upon your work non-commercially, as long as they credit you and license their new creations under the same terms.

In other words, you can copy and redistribute the material in any medium or format, and adapt, remix, transform, and build upon the material. However, you must give credit to the original creator, provide a link to the license, and indicate if changes were made. You must also distribute your contributions under the same license as the original material.

Examples of permitted use:

A student can copy and redistribute an academic article on a blog to discuss their findings.
A professor can adapt an academic article to create an online course.
Examples of prohibited use:

A company cannot use an academic article to promote a product or service related to climate change.